Include assertions: add few assertions in the program
commitResults.messageBody:
There are several assumptions made while running the program.

There are might come situations when these assumptions are not met, but
the program would still be running.

We need a way to alert, the programmer that the program is being run as
expected. Let's add assertion statements at various points in the code,
to make sure our assumptions are met.

This way we would know where we went wrong and what exactly was missing.

Needs to be updated to improve readability.

Let's change the code to better comply with the coding standards and
improve readability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Users can add tasks freely, without being notified if they have any other engagements that day.
commitResults.messageBody:
If there are any clashes the user can be notified so that they are not
double-booked for different tasks at the same time.

Add a feature to warn the users about possible clashes, by modifying the
AddCommand class. New methods have to be added to TaskList, Ui, and
Tasks and its children classes.

Modifying AddCommand class lets us deal with the issue at the
appropriate level.

This means that users could keep adding the same tasks, and this means
that conan stores duplicates of the same task.

Let's Modify the code so that new tasks added are not duplicates. If
they are duplicates then issue a warning to the user, and ask them to
delete the previous task if they would like to add the new task.

Modifying AddCommand and Ui class would help us deal with the problem at
the appropriate level.
Finalize product features and removed dead code.
